-- Bouygues Said to Hire Banks for Sale of 10-Year Bonds in Euros
-- B y   B e n   M a r t i n
-- 2012-01-26T08:03:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-26/bouygues-said-to-hire-banks-for-sale-of-10-year-bonds-in-euros.html
Bouygues SA (EN)  plans to sell 10-year
bonds in euros, according to a banker involved in the
transaction.  BNP Paribas SA, Credit Agricole CIB,  HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA) ,
Natixis, Mitsubishi UFJ Securities International and Societe
Generale SA are managing the deal, the banker said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ben Martin at 
 bmartin38@bloomberg.net  